e (film)|Rushmore]]'' || [[Touchstone Pictures]] and American Empirical Pictures \n|-\n| align=\"right\"| October 16, 1998 || ''[[Beloved (1998 film)|Beloved]]'' || [[Touchstone Pictures]], [[Harpo Productions|Harpo Films]] and <br /> Clinica Estetico \n|-\n| align=\"right\"| November 6, 1998 || ''[[The Waterboy]]'' || [[Touchstone Pictures]] \n|-\n| align=\"right\" | November 13, 1998 || ''[[I'll Be Home for Christmas (1998 film)|I'll Be Home for Christmas]]'' || [[Walt Disney Pictures]] and [[Mandeville Films]] \n|-\n| align=\"right\"| November 20, 1998 || ''[[Enemy of the State (film)|Enemy of the State]]'' || [[Touchstone Pictures]], [[Jerry Bruckheimer Films]] and <br /> [[Scott Free Productions]] \n|-\n| align=\"right\" | November 25, 1998 || ''[[A Bug's Life]]'' || [[Walt Disney Pictures]] and [[Pixar|Pixar Animation Studios]] \n|-\n| align=\"right\" | December 25, 1998 || ''[[Mighty Joe Young (1998 film)|Mighty Joe Young]]'' || [[Walt Disney Pictures]], [[RKO Pictures]] and <br/>The Jacobson Company \n|-\n| align=\"right\"| January 8, 1999 || ''[[A Civil Action (film)|A Civil Action]]'' || [[Touchstone Pictures]], [[Paramount Pictures]] and <br /> [[Wildwood Enterprises, Inc]] \n|-\n| align=\"right\" | February 12, 1999 || ''[[My Favorite Martian (film)|My Favorite Martian]]'' || [[Walt Disney Pictures]] \n|-\n| align=\"right\"| February 26, 1999 || ''[[The Other Sister]]'' || [[Touchstone Pictures]] and [[Mandeville Films]] \n|-\n| align=\"right\" | March 26, 1999 || ''[[Doug's 1st Movie]]'' || [[Walt Disney Pictures]], [[Jumbo Pictures]], <br>[[Disney Television Animation|Walt Disney Television Animation]] and [[Plus One Animation]] \n|-\n| align=\"right\" | March 31, 1999 || ''[[10 Things I Hate About You]]'' || [[Touchstone Pictures]] \n|-\n| align=\"right\" | May 14, 1999 || ''[[Endurance (film)|Endurance]]'' || [[Walt Disney Pictures]] \n|-\n| align=\"right\"| June 4, 1999 || ''[[Instinct (1999 film)|Instinct]]'' || [[Touchstone Pictures]] and [[Spygla