, "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{About|a broader list of Disney films produced by all studios owned by the Walt Disney Studios during their initial release|a list of films only released under the Disney banner|List of Walt Disney Pictures films{{!}}List of Walt Disney Pictures films}}\n{{use American English|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2020}}\n\nThis is a '''list of films''' produced and released by the U.S. film studio '''[[Walt Disney Studios (division)|Walt Disney Studios]]''', one of [[the Walt Disney Company]]'s divisions and one of the [[major film studio|\"Big Five\" major film studios]]. The list include films produced or released by all existing and defunct labels or subsidiaries under the Walt Disney Studios; including [[Walt Disney Pictures]], [[Walt Disney Animation Studios]], [[Pixar|Pixar Animation Studios]], [[Marvel Studios]], [[Lucasfilm]], [[20th Century Fox|20th Century Studios]], [[Searchlight Pictures]], [[Disneynature]], [[Touchstone Pictures]], and [[Hollywood Pictures]]. The list does not include films produced by studios that are now owned by Disney (as part of acquisitions), but were historically not distributed by Disney during their ''original, initial time of release''. \n\nAll films listed are [[Art release|theatrical releases]] unless specified. Films labeled with a '''\u2021''' symbol signifies a [[Streaming media|streaming release]] through [[Disney+]].\n\n==1930s==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Release date\n! Title\n! Studio\n! Notes |\n|-\n| align=\"right\"| May 19, 1937 || ''[[Academy Award Review of Walt Disney Cartoons]]'' || rowspan=\"2\" | [[Walt Disney Pictures|Walt Disney Productions]] || Anthology film; compilation of previously released shorts<ref>Smith, Dave. (2006). ''Disney A to Z: The Official Encyclopedia'' (3rd ed). p. 3. Disney Editions. {{ISBN|978-0786849192}}.</ref>\n|-\n| align=\"right\"| December 21, 1937 || ''[[Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs (1937 